1. Linear algebra intuition (vectors, matrices, transformations)
2. Probability and uncertainty (events, conditional thinking)
3. Distributions and variance
4. Correlation versus causation
5. Sampling theory
6. Error propagation
Maths will be explained visually and intuitively. Formal notation will be introduced gradually. Every formula will include explanation and example.
*/
/*CPD and professional alignment:
1. Aligns with senior professional CPD expectations
2. Anchored in strategic and architectural thinking
3. Supports cross disciplinary leadership without making certification claims
*/
/*CI quality gates for Data Advanced:
1. Each section needs at least 4 long explanatory paragraphs, 1 mathematical concept explained, 1 DiagramBlock, and 1 advanced ToolCard.
2. Include applied reasoning and avoid purely conceptual sections.
3. No unexplained mathematical symbols.
4. No copy pasted content from Foundations or Intermediate.
